Although improved long-term outcomes obtained with the use of arterial grafts 
for coronary revascularization in comparison with the traditional association of 
a single arterial and saphenous vein grafts have been demonstrated in the 
overall population, the efficacy of this newer technique in the elderly is 
difficult to prove because their shorter life expectancy due to advanced heart 
disease, associated with severe comorbidities. Moreover, more widespread use of 
